tart="0" data-end="140">No problem. The easiest way is to make the QR generated by <strong data-start="59" data-end="69">Python</strong>, not by manually uploading images. You only need to edit <strong data-start="127" data-end="139">one file</strong>.</p>
<h2 data-section-id="1w4uphv" data-start="142" data-end="179"><span role="text">Step 1: Open <code data-start="158" data-end="179">upi_qr_generator.py</code></span></h2>
<p data-start="181" data-end="223">Replace everything in that file with this:</p>
